'''12: First, def a function called distance_from_zero, with 
one argument (choose any argument name you like). If 
the type of the argument is either int or float, the 
function should return the absolute value of the function 
input. Otherwise, the function should return "Nope". 
Check if it works calling the function with -5.6 and 
"what?".'''

def distance_from_zero(d):
    if type(d)==int or type(d)==float:
        return abs(d)
    else:
        return "nope"
print(distance_from_zero(-5.6))
print(distance_from_zero("what?"))

